        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>A client accesses one or more Web services that are distributed across a network.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The Web services are designed so that access to additional resources (such as databases or other Web services) is encapsulated in the business logic of the Web service.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>These resources must be protected against unauthorized access.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following illustration depicts a trusted subsystem process.</source>
        </trans-unit>
